results.name: Smallest odd pseudoprimes to base n exceeding n (like A007535 but with smallest odd terms instead of few even ones).
link: Charles R Greathouse IV, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
Index entries for sequences related to pseudoprimes
mathematica: ds[x_, b_] := Mod[ -1+b^(x-1), x] a[n_] := Block[{m=1, s=ds[m, n]}, While[(s !=0||PrimeQ[m])||Equal[m, 1] ||!Greater[m, n]||EvenQ[m], m++ ];m]; t=Table[a[n], {n, 1, 256}]
program: (PARI) a(n)=my(k=n+if(n%2,2,1));while(Mod(n,k)^(k-1)!=1 || isprime(k), k+=2);k \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Apr 12 2012
